===============================
Windows ICACLS Permissions Cheat Sheet
===============================

Permission Letters:

F  : Full control 
     - Read, Write, Execute, Modify, Delete, Change Permissions, Take Ownership

M  : Modify
     - Read, Write, Execute, Delete
     - Cannot change permissions or ownership

RX : Read & Execute
     - Read files
     - Run / execute files
     - Enter folders

R  : Read-only
     - Read files
     - List folder contents

W  : Write-only
     - Add / modify file contents

D  : Delete
     - Delete the file or folder

X  : Execute
     - Run files or scripts
     - Enter folder

T  : Take ownership
     - Used with /grant to allow user to take ownership

===============================
Usage Examples:

# Grant read-only access to a user
icacls "C:\path\to\file.txt" /grant "username:R"

# Grant full control to a user
icacls "C:\path\to\file.txt" /grant "username:F"

# Grant modify access to a user
icacls "C:\path\to\file.txt" /grant "username:M"

# Grant read & execute access
icacls "C:\path\to\file.txt" /grant "username:RX"

# Remove inheritance from a file
icacls "C:\path\to\file.txt" /inheritance:r

# Remove a user's access
icacls "C:\path\to\file.txt" /remove "username"
